    <p>
      We will restrict the domain of
      <m>y=\sin x</m> to the interval <m>[-\frac{\pi}{2},\frac{\pi}{2}]</m>,
      the domain of <m>y=\cos x</m> to <m>[0,\pi]</m>,
      and the domain of <m>y=\tan x</m> to the interval <m>(-\frac{\pi}{2},\frac{\pi}{2})</m>.
      Notice that the domain for each trigonometric function includes one quadrant where the function is positive and one quadrant where it is negative.
    </p>
    <p>
      Domain of <m>y=\sin x</m>:
      <me>
        -\frac{\pi}{2}\leq x\leq\frac{\pi}{2}
      </me>
